subject: p19894745
History: History of breast cancer and cirrhosis. To evaluate for pneumonia or effusion.
Findings: There are multiple relatively discrete mass projected throughout both lobes of the lung. These are concerning for metastatic deposits. Relatively poor inspiratory effort, within these limitations, no definitive effusions are identified. Pneumonic consolidation is not definitively excluded but given the widespread metastasis. Overall little interval change when compared to prior examination. CONCLUSION Little interval changeWidespread metastatic disease.
